description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for an opportunity to consolidate your clinical skills and knowledge as an Occupational Therapist working with the frail older adults and the busy front door?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you keen to develop leadership, managerial and service development roles as a Static Band 6 Occupational Therapist?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, this is the post for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Frailty team at Queens Hospital Burton is pleased to offer an exciting position for a dynamic and enthusiastic Occupational Therapist to work as a Static Band 6 within the team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for a motivated, dynamic and enthusiastic Occupational Therapist with a passion for acute care. You should have excellent communication and interpersonal skills and a commitment to providing high quality care.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be responsible for taking a lead role in the day- to- day working and prioritisation of Occupational Therapy work load within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to have varied clinical experience, including working with elderly patients in an acute multidisciplinary setting. You must also be able to demonstrate experience of supervising students and junior members of staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have a varied post graduate experience in an acute setting and be keen to develop managerial skills. Experience in supporting students and junior staff is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to contribute to a 7 day extended hour service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consolidation and development of assessment and treatment skills to work within the acute site, to include patients with respiratory conditions, diabetes, falls, dementia and cardiac conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consolidation of skills to make quick decisions regarding complex patients in a pressured ED environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consolidation and development of skills to enable close MDT working and discharge planning in a high pressured environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise and support the ongoing development of students, assistants and junior members of the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiation of and involvement in service improvement projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiation of and involvement in clinical and team audit, including notes audits, stats audits and compliance with team clinical standards audits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the Team as required at meetings or training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working within established multidisciplinary teams - close working with the Physiotherapist to ensure safe and timely patient reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience and support with complex discharge planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working alongside Advanced Clinical Practitioners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a friendly and supportive team who can offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support from Therapy Inpatient Lead, Band 7 Team Leaders and Senior Therapists within the team, including regular clinical and managerial supervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Autonomy to provide specialist assessment and treatment to a caseload of patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PT/OT joint working.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support to attend appropriate inservice training opportunities and courses to maintain competencies and to achieve personal development plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trust commitment to CPD, demonstrated by yearly appraisal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In return we will offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development opportunities, including both professional and leadership development, together with an opportunity to work across some or all of our 5 sites depending on specialty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support through every step of the way from recruitment to when you join our team and beyond&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Friendly, supportive and caring colleagues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A variety of other staff benefits including employee assistance programme, discounted gym membership, onsite fitness classes, car schemes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key facts about our Trust: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Every day our hospitals see more than 4,000 outpatients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We see more Trauma &amp; Orthopaedic outpatients than any other Trust – over 3,300 per week&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An average 860 patients are seen in A&amp;E every day – the 6th largest in the country&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Our hospitals admit more than 220 emergency patients every day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We carry out more planned surgical operations than any other Trust in England with almost 50,000 operations taking place in our 52 operating theatres&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are one of only 5 Trusts nationally with more than 50 operating theatres&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We carry out more than 300 elective procedures each working day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We employ 12,000 staff across our 5 hospital sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We have a Director of Allied Health Professionals who is committed to provide leadership, progression and direction to AHPs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date of applications: 16 November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 30 November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to COVID-19 and the Governments guidance on social distancing your interview may be carried out via Microsoft Teams. If this is the case you will be notified in advance so that if you don’t have the app you can download it either on to your phone or computer/laptop. The download is free of charge. Where your interview is face to face, the Trust will ensure social distancing. You will be required to wear a mask on all UHDB premises. If you have Covid-19 related symptoms or are shielding and have been invited for a face to face interview please request a Microsoft Teams interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trac emails can sometimes go in to your junk mail so please check this for feedback on your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Letitia Butler - Inpatient Therapy Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 01283 511511 ext 3037&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lorna Mear - Band 7 Occupational Therapist &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 01283511511 ext 5121&lt;/p&gt;
